Hi, things are going well. 
I apologize for not replying right away, I haven't communicated via toad in a long time, I didn't see what you wrote. 
Now I'm finishing a full report on the Intel ME controller mechanism and the AMT technology based on it. 
A lot of undocumented commands have been recovered using reverse, interaction interface dump and phasing.\Unfortunately the starting theory based on the Embedi/PositiveTechnologies resercher presentation has not been confirmed in the form they presented it, but there is another legal mechanism to activate AMT, but so far it hasn't come to a working POC, at the moment I'm making a buffer sniffer which provides the HECI interface, as it is not a working POC. There are some ideas, if we talk about the topic of the webfi, it is not just a load dropper but maybe some SMM level daemon handlers, plus since I have now studied the ME controller, there are some ideas to test such functionality as overwriting the SPI flash drive through it. Normally this controller is allowed to write to the flash drive, which is not the case with the processor, and some commands have been found that are responsible for this functionality.
